<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="513" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1436,1263,1650]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,1479,1506]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Comments:</emphasis>
Our specimens correspond well with the characteristics mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Miller, W. R. &amp; McInnes, S. J. &amp; Bergstrom, D. M." box="[1103,1326,1479,1506]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" pagination="57 - 64" refId="ref16923" refString="Miller, W. R., McInnes, S. J. &amp; Bergstrom, D. M. (2005) Tardigrades of the Australian Antarctic: Hypsibius heardensis (Eutardigrada: Hypsibiidae: dujardini group) a new species from sub - Antarctic Heard Island. Zootaxa, 1022 (1), 57 - 64. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1022.1.3" type="journal article" year="2005">
Miller 
<emphasis box="[1182,1233,1480,1506]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">et al</emphasis>
. (2005)
</bibRefCitation>
, however without a redescription of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Urbanowicz, 1925)" authorityName="Urbanowicz" authorityYear="1925" baseAuthorityName="Urbanowicz" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[532,1020,1515,1542]" class="Eutardigrada" family="Hypsibiidae" genus="Hypsibius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="convergens">
<emphasis box="[532,780,1516,1542]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Hypsibius convergens</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Urbanowicz, C." box="[798,1012,1515,1542]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" pagination="124 - 142" refId="ref19670" refString="Urbanowicz, C. (1925) Sur la variabilite de Macrobiotus oberhaeuseri. Bulletin biologique de la France et de la Belgique, Paris, 59, 124 - 142." type="journal article" year="1925">Urbanowicz, 1925</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, based on 
<typeStatus box="[1145,1193,1516,1542]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">type</typeStatus>
specimens, a correct identification of this taxon is not possible. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Urbanowicz" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[719,1004,1551,1578]" class="Eutardigrada" family="Hypsibiidae" genus="Hypsibius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Parachela" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" phylum="Tardigrada" rank="species" species="convergens">
<emphasis box="[719,831,1552,1578]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Hypsibius</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis box="[878,1004,1552,1577]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">convergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a cosmopolitan distribution (Mc- Innes 1994), but it is probably a species complex. In 
<collectingCountry box="[824,912,1587,1613]" name="Mexico" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, this species was reported from Creel, Cuiteco and Temoris in the State of 
<collectingRegion box="[535,656,1623,1649]" country="Mexico" name="Chihuahua" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Chihuahua</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schuster, R. O." box="[671,836,1623,1650]" pageId="12" pageNumber="513" pagination="213 - 224" refId="ref19022" refString="Schuster, R. O. (1971) Tardigrada from the Barranca del Cobre Sinaloa and Chihuahua, Mexico. Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 84, 213 - 224." type="journal article" year="1971">Schuster 1971</bibRefCitation>
). This is a new record for the State of 
<collectingRegion box="[1263,1406,1624,1650]" country="Mexico" name="Nuevo Leon" pageId="12" pageNumber="513">Nuevo Leon</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
